SIMPLE: mix_up
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: mix up
<hw>mix up</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To confuse the identities
of (two or more objects); to mistake (one object for another); <as>as,
at the family gathering he <ex>mixed up</ex> his two nieces, to their
great amusement</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To mix together; -- usually implying a mistake,
whether done intentionally or unintentionally; <as>as, the <ex>mixed
up</ex> this year's receipts with last year's, and it took hours to find
the right ones</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>mix-up</ent>⟦br⟧
